\par
\b\fs24 12. FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Q: What if no vehicles are available for a trip?\par
\b0 A: Check if any maintenance vehicles can be expedited. Otherwise, reject the request with explanation or suggest alternative dates.\par
\par
\b Q: How do I handle emergency vehicle requests?\par
\b0 A: Contact department head directly. You may need to reassign vehicles from lower-priority trips.\par
\par
\b Q: Can I assign a different vehicle than requested?\par
\b0 A: Yes, you have full discretion. Consider trip requirements, passenger count, and vehicle suitability.\par
\par
\b Q: What happens when I approve a request?\par
\b0 A: The requester receives notification, vehicle is marked "reserved," and driver is notified of assignment.\par
\par
\b Q: How do I handle a driver calling in sick?\par
\b0 A: Update driver status to Unavailable. Reassign any affected trips to available drivers. Notify requesters of any changes.\par
\par
\b Q: Can I modify an approved trip's vehicle or driver?\par
\b0 A: Yes, as Motorpool Head you can override assignments for approved requests. Notify the requester of changes.\par
\par
\b Q: What reports should I generate regularly?\par
\b0 A: Weekly vehicle usage reports and monthly driver performance reports are recommended for fleet optimization.\par
